rs might have had some idea that something a bit shady was going on:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hedge fund investors who received =
confidential information from the Head of the Desk and Employee-1 about upc=
oming blocks recognized that this information allowed them to profit in way=
s they otherwise would not have. For example, an investor working at a Neva=
da- based hedge fund (=E2=80=9CInvestor-3=E2=80=9D) told the Head of the De=
sk in an August 2021 call, =E2=80=9CI know who my daddy is,=E2=80=9D referr=
ing to the assistance that the Head of the Desk had provided Investor-3 in =
profiting from block trades.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You don=E2=80=99t say =E2=80=9CI know who my d=
addy is=E2=80=9D to your salesperson unless you know you are getting some s=
ort of weird personal favor.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I=E2=80=99m not sure that=E2=80=99s true f=
or all of them? In general, if someone from a sales or syndicate desk at a =
big bank calls you and says =E2=80=9Chey we have a bunch of Stock X coming,=
 you want some,=E2=80=9D you don=E2=80=99t necessarily have any reason to t=
hink that the salesperson is doing anything nefarious. His job is to sell y=
ou stock! If he calls you up asking if you want to buy stock, you might ass=
ume that he=E2=80=99s just doing his job. You might assume that he is shopp=
ing around the shares with the seller=E2=80=99s permission, that he is tryi=
ng to drum up interest by making the sale public.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean, you might not, because actually with a=
 block trade that would be kind of weird. (The salesperson <em>might=C2=A0<=
/em>call you in advance with the company=E2=80=99s permission, but ordinari=
ly he=E2=80=99d =E2=80=9Cwall-cross=E2=80=9D you first, making you agree no=
t to trade until the sale is public.) And if you got a call from a salesper=
son saying =E2=80=9CI have some Stock X to sell, you want some,=E2=80=9D an=
d you=C2=A0hung up and immediately=C2=A0<em>shorted the stock yourself</em>=
