th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  Sridhar Natarajan and Katherine Burton report</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When the US punished Morgan Stanley for leakin=
g upcoming stock trades to favored clients, it kept the list of recipients =
secret. They include one of Wall Street=E2=80=99s biggest players: Citadel.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A trader at Ken Griffin=E2=80=99s giant hedge =
fund was among a coterie of executives described anonymously in Morgan Stan=
ley=E2=80=99s settlements with the government, according to people with kno=
wledge of the matter. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Prosecutors haven=E2=80=99t accused any buy-si=
de participants that allegedly received tips of any wrongdoing. =E2=80=A6</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not every leak resulted in hedge fund managers=
 trading before blocks of stock were sold. In some cases the sellers aborte=
d their plans, which is what happened on two trades that were leaked to Cit=
adel. Industry lawyers also argued that if firms did trade, they didn=E2=80=
=99t break any laws, because they hadn=E2=80=99t signed confidentiality pac=
ts with the bank.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hedge funds on the receiving end of informatio=
n from a Morgan Stanley executive were =E2=80=9Centitled to assume he was f=
ollowing his firm=E2=80=99s rules,=E2=80=9D said Cristie Ford, a former Dav=
is Polk lawyer who now teaches at the University of British Columbia. The n=
ature of interactions is such that =E2=80=9Csome of it is based on rumors, =
some of it is based on hunches, and some of it is based on hypothetical que=
stions from equity desks.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I do think that's basically right. If you meet=
 your buddy from Morgan Stanley on the golf course and he says =E2=80=9Chey=
 I=E2=80=99ve got a hot tip for you, don=E2=80=99t tell anyone,=E2=80=9D yo=
u can assume he=E2=80=99s up to no good. If he calls you at your desk, from=
 his desk, on a recorded line, saying =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99ve got a deal com=
ing and we=E2=80=99d like you to be in it,=E2=80=9D I think you=E2=80=99re =
allowed to assume it=E2=80=99s fine. Even though, here, it was not.</p>
